Nakuru Governor Kinuthia Mbugua (pictured) has struck a deal with President Uhuru Kenyatta to be appointed to the Cabinet, sources told the Star Yesterday.The sources said the deal was struck after Uhuru, DP William Ruto and Mbugua met on Saturday in Nakuru State House. The sources, who sought anonymity, said, &ldquo;It took the President and his deputy to convince Mbugua to step down and support Lee Kinyanjui, who the leaders felt is the best choice and appeals to voters.&rdquo; Mbugua said he was opting out of the race because of the respect he has for Uhuru.